OL,3,CD-Day 80 The Last Veterans: Peter
OL,4,CSmoothy
OL,6,FHe said: "We eventually got into the
OL,7,Fbeach about half past eight. We
OL,8,Fcouldn't get in, there just wasn't
OL,9,Froom for us all to get in. It was
OL,10,Freasonably quiet on the beach because
OL,11,Fthe fighting had gone away from the
OL,12,Fedge so they were fighting some of
OL,13,Fthem miles away.
OL,15,F"There were shells going that way and
OL,16,Fthat way and every time we heard one
OL,17,Fwe said 'well that one's not mine,
OL,18,Fthat one's not mine' because they'd
OL,19,Fcome and gone before you realised what
OL,20,Fthey were.
OL,1,W h7}h7}j7}h7}h7}                 G5/7
